# Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ) ❓

## What is LLM Studio?
LLM Studio is an AI-powered platform that helps you design, generate, and deploy decentralized applications quickly and securely.

## How does the AI code generation work?
You provide natural language descriptions of the dApp you want, and our AI models generate optimized smart contract code and frontend components.

## Which blockchains does LLM Studio support?
Currently, Ethereum, Binance Smart Chain, and Polygon are supported, with plans to add more networks.

## Do I need coding experience to use LLM Studio?
No. The platform is designed to enable users of all skill levels to build dApps using natural language commands.

## How does LLM Studio ensure security?
We integrate static and dynamic analysis tools, run extensive simulations, and support formal verification to safeguard your dApps.

## Is there a token associated with LLM Studio?
Yes, the LST token fuels platform usage, governance, staking, and rewards.

## How can I deploy my dApp?
After reviewing and testing generated code, you can deploy directly through the platform’s interface to your chosen blockchain network.

## What kind of support is available?
We offer detailed documentation, tutorials, and a community forum to help you every step of the way.

## Can I update my deployed dApps?
Yes, LLM Studio supports upgradeable smart contracts and manages updates via secure mechanisms.

## What is the roadmap for future development?
Our roadmap includes expanding blockchain support, enhanced AI features, marketplace launch, and community governance tools—detailed in our roadmap document.

## How do I get involved with the community?
Join our developer forums, participate in governance, and contribute to ecosystem growth via partnerships and community programs.

## Is LLM Studio open source?
Core components are open for community review and contributions to foster transparency and innovation.

## Are there fees to use the platform?
Usage fees apply based on service consumption paid in LST tokens; details are available in the tokenomics document.

## How do I start?
Create an account on our platform, start a new project with natural language descriptions, and let LLM Studio guide you through the process.

## Where can I learn more?
Visit our website and documentation portals for the latest updates, tutorials, and support channels.